@Node scm302
@Title "Compiler Message 302"
Warning 302:  Type punning involves representation change symbol

A variable defined with one type was used with a different type.  This
practice is known as type punning.  This message can occur, for example,
when an assignment is made to a member of a union and then the value is
accessed from a different member of the union.
@EndNode

@Node scm303
@Title "Compiler Message 303"
Warning 303:  Reference has overlapped definition symbol

The indicated identifier has at least two definitions that partially
overlap its storage.
